summary: I got annoyed with that post about All Star in the Captain Marvel film - a song released in 1999 isn’t a nineties song! So I...
caption:
I got annoyed with that post about All Star in the Captain Marvel film - a song released in 1999 isn’t a nineties song!

So I made a playlist of songs released between ‘88 and ‘97 (because stylistic trends don’t line up neatly with actual decades).

  1. Massive Attack - Safe From Harm
  2. Tricky - Black Steel
  3. Nine Inch Nails - Down In It
  4. The Prodigy - Fuel My Fire
  5. Rammstein - Engel
  6. 1000 Homo DJs - Supernaut
  7. Megadeth - Hangar 18
  8. Clutch - Escape From The Prison Planet
  9. Monster Magnet - Negasonic Teenage Warhead
  10. Faith No More - From Out Of Nowhere
  11. Garbage - Supervixen
  12. Veruca Salt - Volcano Girls
  13. Pat Benatar - All Fired Up
  14. No Doubt - The Climb

Listen to it on Spotify
